    "eyebrow": "Summary",
    "num": "10",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">10</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Key Takeaways on Texican Origins</h2><ul><li>'Texican' reflects a unique cultural identity blending indigenous, Spanish, and Mexican roots</li><li>The term derives from the Caddo word 'tejas' meaning 'friends' or 'allies'</li><li>Texican identity was shaped by frontier life and shifting political landscapes</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Understanding the term 'Texican' and its origins is essential to grasp the cultural and historical complexity of early Texas. This identity was forged through linguistic blending, cultural fusion, and political negotiation on the frontier. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texicans exemplified how cultural identities evolve in response to geography, history, and politics.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Summarize in your own words why Texican identity is distinct and important.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid oversimplifying Texican identity as just Mexican or Spanish.</p></div></div>",
