    "num": "19",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Adaptation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How Texicans Adapted to Frontier Challenges</h2><ul><li>Blended agricultural techniques to suit local climate and soil</li><li>Adopted indigenous knowledge for hunting and land management</li><li>Developed social networks for mutual defense and resource sharing</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans demonstrated flexibility by combining diverse cultural practices and forming cooperative communities to overcome environmental and social challenges. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Using indigenous irrigation methods improved crop yields in arid areas.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how cultural adaptation contributed to Texican survival and identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans relied solely on Spanish methods without local innovation.</p></div></div>",
