    "num": "22",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Deep Dive: Ranching Economy</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">The Central Role of Cattle Ranching in Texican Life</h2><ul><li>Ranching provided food, trade goods, and economic stability</li><li>Cattle drives and branding were key practices</li><li>Ranching shaped social hierarchies and land use</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Cattle ranching was more than an economic activity; it influenced Texican social structures and interactions with the environment. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican ranchers used branding to assert ownership and organize herds, a practice blending Spanish and indigenous customs.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how ranching practices affected Texican community organization.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating ranching’s influence on social and economic life.</p></div></div>",
