    "num": "28",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Military Contributions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Fighters and Their Military Roles</h2><ul><li>Texicans served as soldiers, scouts, and leaders in revolutionary battles</li><li>They brought knowledge of local terrain and Spanish military tactics</li><li>Their contributions were vital in key engagements like San Jacinto</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans contributed significantly to the military efforts during the Texas Revolution, leveraging their local knowledge and experience. Their roles ranged from frontline combatants to strategic leaders, influencing the course of battles. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> At the Battle of San Jacinto, Texican troops under Juan Seguín played a decisive role in the Texan victory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texican military skills and knowledge affected battle outcomes.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the strategic importance of Texican fighters due to Anglo-centric historical narratives.</p></div></div>",
