    "eyebrow": "Texican Participation in Key Battles",
    "num": "31",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Participation in Key Battles</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Roles in Major Revolutionary Engagements</h2><ul><li>Siege of Bexar (1835): Texicans fought to capture San Antonio</li><li>Battle of the Alamo (1836): Texicans defended alongside Anglo settlers</li><li>Battle of San Jacinto (1836): Texican troops contributed to decisive victory</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans actively participated in major battles of the Texas Revolution, demonstrating military commitment and strategic importance in the fight for independence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> During the Siege of Bexar, Texican militias helped secure San Antonio from Mexican forces, setting the stage for subsequent battles.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Map Texican involvement across these battles and assess their impact on the revolution's outcome.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Neglecting Texican contributions in favor of focusing solely on Anglo combatants.</p></div></div>",
