    "eyebrow": "Texican Political Challenges",
    "num": "32",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texican Political Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Post-Revolution Political Struggles for Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced marginalization in new Texan government structures</li><li>Conflicts arose over land rights, citizenship, and cultural recognition</li><li>Some Texicans advocated for inclusion and protection of their communities</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">After the revolution, Texicans encountered political challenges as Anglo settlers dominated governance, leading to disputes over rights and identity within the new Republic of Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> José Antonio Navarro worked to secure land titles and political representation for Texicans in the Texas legislature.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how post-revolution political dynamics affected Texican communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican political influence remained strong and unchallenged after independence.</p></div></div>",
