    "eyebrow": "Reflection and Discussion",
    "num": "36",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">36</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection and Discussion</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Considering Texican Identity in Historical Context</h2><ul><li>Texican identity was shaped by cultural blending and political challenges</li><li>Their role in the Texas Revolution was complex and multifaceted</li><li>Understanding Texicans requires critical engagement with diverse sources</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflecting on Texican history encourages learners to appreciate the complexities of identity, loyalty, and historical interpretation in early Texas history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Discuss how Texican experiences illustrate broader themes of cultural hybridity and contested nationhood.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on how Texican identity challenges simple historical narratives.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying Texican history without acknowledging its contested nature.</p></div></div>",
