    "eyebrow": "Source Analysis Practice",
    "num": "43",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">43</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Source Analysis Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating a Land Grant Document</h2><ul><li>Identify the land’s location and size.</li><li>Note legal language and conditions.</li><li>Consider implications for Texican settlement.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Evaluating a land grant helps learners understand legal frameworks and settlement patterns affecting Texicans. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A grant specifying acreage and obligations reveals government control and settler rights.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> What does this document tell us about Texican land ownership and governance?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not overlook legal jargon that affects interpretation.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide43\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39;?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A term referring to early settlers of Texas with Spanish and Mexican cultural roots&quot;,&quot;A nickname for all residents of modern Texas regardless of background&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe indigenous to Texas&quot;,&quot;A group of Anglo-American settlers who moved to Texas after 1836&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; specifically refers to early Texas settlers of Spanish and Mexican heritage, reflecting their unique cultural identity.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the Texicans&#39; cultural background influenced their role in the Texas Revolution.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should describe the Texicans&#39; Spanish and Mexican heritage, their settlement in Spanish Texas, and how their cultural identity led to complex political loyalties during the Texas Revolution. The answer should mention their participation in key events and the contested nature of their allegiance.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;The Texicans, being of Spanish and Mexican descent, settled in Spanish Texas and developed a unique cultural identity blending indigenous and colonial influences. During the Texas Revolution, their loyalties were complex; some supported independence while others remained loyal to Mexico. Their cultural background influenced their participation in battles like the Alamo and shaped early Texas history.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;The Texicans had Spanish and Mexican roots and lived in Spanish Texas; their cultural identity made their political loyalties during the revolution complex, with some supporting independence and others loyal to Mexico.&quot;,&quot;Because of their mixed heritage and settlement patterns, Texicans played a nuanced role in the Texas Revolution, participating in key events and showing divided loyalties.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
