    "eyebrow": "Critical Thinking",
    "num": "47",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">47</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Critical Thinking</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating Historical Interpretations of Texicans</h2><ul><li>Historians debate Texican political loyalties.</li><li>Interpretations vary based on source emphasis.</li><li>Critical evaluation requires weighing evidence.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Understanding contested interpretations helps learners appreciate the complexity of Texican history and the role of evidence in shaping narratives. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some historians emphasize Texican loyalty to Mexico, others highlight their role in Texas independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider how primary sources support or challenge different interpretations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid accepting a single interpretation without critical analysis.</p></div></div>",
