    "num": "51",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">51</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Legacy and Historical Memory</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Legacy in Texas History</h2><ul><li>Texicans contributed to Texas culture, law, and land practices</li><li>Their legacy is often overshadowed by Anglo narratives</li><li>Modern interpretations seek to recover and honor Texican contributions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texicans' cultural and political contributions have been historically underrepresented, but recent scholarship aims to acknowledge their lasting impact on Texas identity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican land grant traditions influenced Texas property laws still in use today.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Reflect on why some historical groups' contributions might be marginalized in mainstream narratives.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking Texican influence by focusing solely on Anglo settler achievements.</p></div></div>",
